casebody.data:
STATE of Iowa, Plaintiff-Appellee,
v.
Kamesha HOUSTON, Defendant-Appellant. No. 18-0070 Court of Appeals of Iowa. Filed January 9, 2019

DECISION WITHOUT PUBLISHED OPINION See Iowa R. App. P. 6.904

Kamesha Houston appeals her convictions for possession of marijuana and carrying weapons, claiming a lack of factual basis for the carrying-weapons plea, and the court erred in sentencing. VACATED IN PART AND REMANDED.

VACATED IN PART. REMANDED.
